The measurement were performed using
a vacuum chamber with a sample in its centre and
a silicon surface barrier telescope detector mounted
outside the neutron beam.

detector-area 150 mm**2, alpha energy resolution
50 keV and a 500-micron thick E-detector, area 450
mm**2, alpha energy resolution 19 keV. The energy
calibration of the detector was done using the well-
known energies of the B-10(n,alpha)Li-7,
Li-6(n,alpha)T, Nd-143(n,alpha)Ce-140 reactions and of
the U-234, U-235 and Cf-252 radioactive decay alphas
